1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,680
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:04,680
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:09,960
My name is Catherine and today we're talking a little bit about food and about your health.
我是Catherine，今天我们聊一聊食物和健康。

4
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:10,960
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:14,680
Today we're going to take a look at our favorite maybe kind of food.
今天我们要看看我们可能最喜欢的某种食物。

6
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:19,840
We're taking a look at the fast food, all these yummy but not very healthy types of
我们要看看快餐，这些美味但不太健康的

7
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,840
food.
食物。

8
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:21,840
Yeah, we are.
是的，我们确实要聊这个。

9
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:25,140
So let's listen to our dialogue and when we come back we'll be talking about what some
那么让我们先听一段对话，等我们回来后会讨论其中一些食物

10
00:00:25,140 --> 00:00:34,640
of these foods are and what some of the phrases you've heard mean.
以及你听到的一些短语是什么意思。

11
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:35,640
I'm hungry.
我饿了。

12
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,400
Let's order up something to eat.
我们点些吃的吧。

13
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:38,400
Okay.
好的。

14
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:41,440
Maybe we can order a soup and a salad from the restaurant down the street.
也许我们可以从街那头的餐厅点一份汤和一份沙拉。

15
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:45,660
I was thinking of getting a hamburger, fries and a chocolate sundae.
我想点一个汉堡、薯条和一个巧克力圣代。

16
00:00:45,660 --> 00:00:47,360
You eat too much junk food.
你吃太多垃圾食品了。

17
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:51,240
That sort of stuff clogs up your arteries and is very high in cholesterol.
那种东西会堵塞你的动脉，而且胆固醇很高。

18
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,480
Well I never seem to gain weight so I don't mind.
嗯，我好像从来不会发胖，所以我不介意。

19
00:00:53,480 --> 00:00:57,180
It's not only about getting fat or not, it's about being healthy.
这不只是胖不胖的问题，而是健康的问题。

20
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:59,440
You could really have some health problems later on.
你以后真的可能会有一些健康问题。

21
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,640
How about pizza or maybe some fried chicken?
披萨或者炸鸡怎么样？

22
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,080
Better yet, let's order some hot dogs.
更好的是，我们点些热狗吧。

23
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:07,320
You're a lost cause.
你真是无可救药了。

24
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,440
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

25
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:15,400
So now let's take a look at language takeaway.
现在让我们来看看语言要点。

26
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,820
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

27
00:01:17,820 --> 00:01:21,680
So first up on language takeaway is a very unhealthy food.
语言要点的第一个是一种非常不健康的食物。

28
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,720
It's called a chocolate sundae.
它叫做巧克力圣代。

29
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:24,720
That's right.
没错。

30
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:27,680
We wanted to order hamburger, french fries and a chocolate sundae.
我们想点汉堡、薯条和巧克力圣代。

31
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:32,280
So chocolate we know that this is the flavor that comes from cocoa.
巧克力我们知道这是来自可可的味道。

32
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,200
But what is a sundae?
但什么是圣代？

33
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:38,680
Well basically a sundae is a kind of ice cream dessert.
基本上圣代是一种冰淇淋甜点。

34
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:45,640
It comes in a cup or a bowl and it's usually vanilla ice cream with chocolate sauce and
它装在一个杯子或碗里，通常是香草冰淇淋配上巧克力酱，

35
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:49,360
then oftentimes a cherry on top.
然后经常在上面放一颗樱桃。

36
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:56,200
So as you can see the word is pronounced exactly like the day, sundae, but it has a different
所以你可以看到这个词的发音和“星期天”完全一样，但结尾拼写不同。

37
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,000
spelling in the end.
结尾拼写不同。

38
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,400
S-U-N-D-A-E, sundae.
S-U-N-D-A-E，圣代。

39
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,940
So this is a chocolate sundae.
所以这就是巧克力圣代。

40
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:07,240
So when you see this spelling, a sundae with an E, that's the dessert.
所以当你看到这种拼写，带E的圣代，那就是甜点。

41
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,560
If you see it with a Y, that's the day.
如果你看到带Y的，那就是星期天。

42
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,560
Exactly.
没错。

43
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:14,360
So chocolate sundae, actually a very delicious dessert, but remember it's ice cream.
所以巧克力圣代，其实是一种非常美味的甜点，但记住它是冰淇淋。

44
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,360
That's right.
没错。

45
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:21,040
And all of these types of food, hamburger, chocolate sundae, it's called junk food.
所有这些食物，汉堡、巧克力圣代，都叫做垃圾食品。

46
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,040
Junk food.
垃圾食品。

47
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,040
Well food you know.
嗯，食物你知道。

48
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,040
Junk.
垃圾。

49
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,040
What is an example of junk, Marco?
什么是垃圾的例子，Marco？

50
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:28,640
Well something that's not good or useful anymore.
嗯，就是不再有用或不再好的东西。

51
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:33,320
So maybe you have trash that you need to get rid of, like an old TV.
比如你有一些需要扔掉的垃圾，像一台旧电视。

52
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,440
That's junk.
那就是垃圾。

53
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:38,240
So my mom would always say, throw away this junk.
所以我妈妈总是会说，扔掉这些垃圾。

54
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,580
It's stuff that you don't need.
就是你不用的东西。

55
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:42,120
So junk is things that you would throw away.
所以垃圾就是你会扔掉的东西。

56
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,320
Junk food is the kind of food that's not healthy for you.
垃圾食品就是对你健康不好的那种食物。

57
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:48,800
It's the food that you shouldn't eat, but it tends to be really delicious.
就是你不该吃的食物，但它往往非常美味。

58
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,800
That's right.
没错。

59
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:55,680
So for example, the hamburger, french fries, a chocolate sundae, all this would fall under
所以比如汉堡、薯条、巧克力圣代，这些都归入

60
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:58,520
this category of junk food.
垃圾食品这一类。

61
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,520
That's right.
没错。

62
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:02,800
And one of the things about junk food is that it's high in cholesterol.
垃圾食品的一个特点是它胆固醇很高。

63
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,760
Now what is cholesterol, Marco?
什么是胆固醇，Marco？

64
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,760
That's right.
没错。

65
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,760
So you always have to be careful.
所以你总是要小心。

66
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:12,120
Your doctor says that you shouldn't have or you have to be careful about having high cholesterol.
你的医生会说你不应该有高胆固醇，或者要小心高胆固醇。

67
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:18,680
And that's just basically, it's a type of fat that is found in animal products.
基本上，它是一种在动物产品中发现的脂肪。

68
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:24,560
So for example, beef has cholesterol and it's dangerous because it could maybe cause health
比如牛肉含有胆固醇，它很危险，因为可能会导致健康问题。

69
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,560
problems.
健康问题。

70
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,560
That's right.
没错。

71
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:33,000
So my friend needed to lower his cholesterol and his doctor told him he should eat less
所以我的朋友需要降低胆固醇，他的医生告诉他应该少吃

72
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,880
red meat, eat more vegetables and fruits instead.
红肉，多吃蔬菜和水果。

73
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:37,880
That's right.
没错。

74
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:41,560
So cholesterol is a, you'll see it all the time when you're shopping.
所以胆固醇是，你购物时会经常看到。

75
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:47,040
You'll see that it's low in cholesterol or no sugar or no calories, stuff like that.
你会看到低胆固醇、无糖或无卡路里之类的标签。

76
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,040
Exactly.
没错。

77
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:54,480
Now, a food that is very, very high in cholesterol is fried chicken, but it's also very delicious.
现在，一种胆固醇非常非常高的食物是炸鸡，但它也非常美味。

78
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,480
That's right.
没错。

79
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,480
Fried chicken.
炸鸡。

80
00:03:56,480 --> 00:04:04,540
Now as you see, the first word there is fried and that means that it was cooked in hot oil.
如你所见，第一个词是“炸”，意思是用热油烹制的。

81
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:05,540
That's right.
没错。

82
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:09,440
And what's important to remember about most American fried chicken is that the chicken
关于大多数美式炸鸡，需要记住的重要一点是，鸡肉

83
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:18,000
is usually put in a batter, so like a milk, egg, flour sauce, and then it's fried.
通常裹上面糊，也就是牛奶、鸡蛋、面粉调成的酱，然后油炸。

84
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,700
So on the outside it's very, very crispy and salty.
所以外面非常非常酥脆和咸。

85
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:22,700
That's right.
没错。

86
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:27,480
So it's covered in like a type of bread, like a crispy bread.
所以它外面裹着一层像面包一样的东西，脆脆的面包。

87
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,520
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

88
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:34,440
It's usually very greasy, so when you eat it, you have lots of grease on your fingers.
通常很油腻，所以吃的时候手指上会有很多油。

89
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:39,200
But one of the reasons it tastes so good is because as you say, Marco, it's fried in oil.
但味道这么好的原因之一，正如你所说，马可，是因为它在油里炸过。

90
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,040
That's right.
没错。

91
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,040
Very good.
很好。

92
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:45,560
So this is all the vocab that we have for language takeaway.
这就是我们“语言摘录”部分的所有词汇。

93
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:53,080
Let's listen to the dialogue again.
让我们再听一遍对话。

94
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,080
I'm hungry.
我饿了。

95
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,880
Let's order up something to eat.
我们点些吃的吧。

96
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:59,960
Okay, maybe we can order a soup and a salad from the restaurant down the street.
好吧，也许我们可以从街那头的餐厅点一份汤和一份沙拉。

97
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:04,200
I was thinking of getting a hamburger, fries, and a chocolate sundae.
我在想点一个汉堡、薯条和一个巧克力圣代。

98
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,880
You eat too much junk food.
你吃太多垃圾食品了。

99
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:09,240
That sort of stuff clogs up your arteries and is very high in cholesterol.
那种东西会堵塞你的动脉，而且胆固醇很高。

100
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:12,000
Well, I never seem to gain weight, so I don't mind.
嗯，我好像从来不会长胖，所以我不介意。

101
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,680
It's not only about getting fat or not, it's about being healthy.
这不只是长胖不长胖的问题，而是关于健康。

102
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:18,720
You could really have some health problems later on.
你以后真的可能会有一些健康问题。

103
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:21,280
How about pizza or maybe some fried chicken?
披萨或者炸鸡怎么样？

104
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,560
Better yet, let's order some hot dogs.
更好的是，我们点些热狗吧。

105
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:28,080
You're a lost cause.
你真是无可救药了。

106
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:33,320
All right, now it's time for some phrases on Fluency Builder.
好了，现在是“流利度构建”部分的一些短语。

107
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:35,320
Fluency Builder
流利度构建

108
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:39,520
So one of the first phrases is actually something that I'm excited to talk about because it
第一个短语其实是我很兴奋要讲的，因为它

109
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:43,560
comes up a lot in directions when we're giving people directions somewhere.
在指路时经常出现，当我们给别人指路时。

110
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:49,520
So one of the people in the dialogue said, we can order a soup and salad from the restaurant
对话中有一个人说，我们可以从街那头的餐厅点一份汤和沙拉。

111
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,040
down the street.
没错。

112
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,040
Right.
对。

113
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:56,000
So this is, you're basically telling the person where the restaurant is.
所以这基本上是在告诉别人餐厅的位置。

114
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:00,600
And when you say something is down the street, it means that it's nearby.
当你说某物在“down the street”时，意思是它就在附近。

115
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,600
It is.
是的。

116
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,600
It's nearby.
就在附近。

117
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:08,720
It's on the same street or it's just a few minutes walk from where you are now.
在同一条街上，或者离你现在的位置只有几分钟的步行路程。

118
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,720
Right, right.
对，对。

119
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:14,280
So you can say, my apartment is just down the street from this park.
所以你可以说，我的公寓就在这个公园的街那头。

120
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,320
So it's very close.
所以非常近。

121
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,440
Or you could say, I know him.
或者你可以说，我认识他。

122
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:20,880
He lived down the street from me when we were children.
我们小时候他就住在我家街那头。

123
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,160
Okay, so he lived really, really close to you.
好的，所以他住得离你非常非常近。

124
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,160
Very good.
很好。

125
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:30,520
Now, when we were talking about junk food and we were talking about how it's not healthy,
现在，当我们谈论垃圾食品以及它不健康时，

126
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:34,840
we said that junk food clogs up your arteries.
我们说垃圾食品会堵塞你的动脉。

127
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,080
All right.
好的。

128
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,920
A couple important words here to clog up arteries.
这里有几个重要的词，“clog up arteries”。

129
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,880
The verb to clog, what does that mean?
动词“clog”是什么意思？

130
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:48,880
Clog with a G. It means it gets in the way or obstructs it.
“Clog”带G，意思是阻碍或堵塞。

131
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,880
All right.
好的。

132
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:56,440
So for example, if a drain, in my sink, if a drain is clogged, the water does not go
比如，如果我水槽里的排水管堵了，水就流不

133
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,440
down.
下去。

134
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:58,440
Right.
对。

135
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,840
So the water starts to build and build and build.
所以水会越积越多。

136
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:04,080
Actually, it's very dangerous because if it comes up too much, the water will go on the
实际上，这很危险，因为如果水太多，就会流到

137
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,640
floor.
地板上。

138
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,600
But that's a drain, that's a sink.
但那是排水管，那是水槽。

139
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:12,760
If you're talking about the heart, you would say that cholesterol clogs up your arteries.
如果你在说心脏，你会说胆固醇堵塞你的动脉。

140
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:13,760
Right.
对。

141
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:17,800
So your arteries are like these tubes where blood passes.
所以你的动脉就像血液流过的管道。

142
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:21,520
And of course, if they're clogged up, then blood can't pass.
当然，如果它们被堵塞了，血液就无法通过。

143
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,520
That's right.
没错。

144
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:27,880
And if it's very serious, people sometimes have to have heart surgery to clear those
如果情况很严重，人们有时需要做心脏手术来清理这些

145
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:33,360
arteries to take the blockage, the clogging away from the arteries.
动脉，移除堵塞物。

146
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,360
That's right.
没错。

147
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,360
That's right.
没错。

148
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,360
Okay.
好的。

149
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:39,840
So that is to clog something up or something is clogged up.
所以这就是“to clog something up”或“something is clogged up”。

150
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:45,480
Now moving on, when we were giving suggestions, we said, all right, well, how about pizza
现在继续，当我们提建议时，我们说，好吧，披萨

151
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,600
or maybe some fried chicken?
或者炸鸡怎么样？

152
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:50,160
Better yet, let's order some hot dogs.
更好的是，我们点些热狗吧。

153
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,160
All right.
好的。

154
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:55,240
Now this is a great phrase, as you say, Marco, for offering a suggestion.
正如你所说，马可，这是一个很好的提建议的短语。

155
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,840
You could say, I think we should eat hamburgers.
你可以说，我觉得我们应该吃汉堡。

156
00:07:58,840 --> 00:07:59,840
Better yet.
更好的是。

157
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:00,840
Okay.
好的。

158
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:01,840
So what does this mean?
所以这是什么意思？

159
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:07,000
